videos.description: Ignas Brazdeikis attacks the paint and goes right at Jordan Bohannon, nailing the bank shot through contact for a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Brazdeikis goes through Bohannon for and-1

videos.description: Nicholas Baer draws the double team and finds an open Joe Wieskamp, who flushes down a two-handed slam to extend the Hawkeyes' lead.
videos.headline: Wieskamp hammers down two-handed dunk

videos.description: Jordan Bohannon swings a pass to Nicholas Baer, who sinks a 3-pointer from well beyond the arc to continue Iowa's scorching start against Michigan.
videos.headline: Baer buries deep 3 for Iowa

videos.description: Zavier Simpson puts a nasty crossover move on Connor McCaffery, then scoops home a tough finger roll for a Michigan bucket.
videos.headline: Simpson shakes and bakes for crafty finish

videos.description: Jordan Poole drives the lane and hooks a pass down low to Jon Teske, who finishes through contact for a big 3-point play.
videos.headline: Poole finds Teske for and-1

videos.description: Joe Wieskamp gets into the paint and challenges two Michigan defenders at the rim, somehow banking in a reverse layup for the 3-point play.
videos.headline: Wieskamp finishes through two defenders for reverse and-1

videos.description: Joe Wieskamp lobs it in to Luka Garza, who elevates for the huge two-handed slam to extend Iowa's second-half lead over Michigan.
videos.headline: Garza throws down rim-rocking slam

videos.description: The Hawkeyes emerge with a 74-59 upset win over the Wolverines, and the crowd at Carver Hawkeye Arena storms the court after the final buzzer.
videos.headline: Iowa fans storm court after knocking off No. 5 Michigan
